1. To check node js install or not, check node -v
2. If you are installing angular js for the first time ,then open terminal and type
	--> " sudo npm install -g @angular/cli " (words inside double quotes)
3. then inside html folder or www folder (first close the terminal and open new terminal from www or html folder) open terminal there and type --->
	"sudo ng new myapp"  (here myapp is the name of project or name of folder just like calisto, so change myapp to any name you want)

4. After finishing you will get a folder of that name that you created.



